<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>The <code>autocapitalize</code> attribute controls whether and how the virtual keyboard automatically capitalizes text as the user types. It affects only mobile and tablet virtual keyboards — physical keyboards and desktop browsers are unaffected.</p>
<p><strong>Applies to:</strong> <a href="/docs/elements/native/input/"><code>&lt;input&gt;</code></a> (text types), <a href="/docs/elements/native/textarea/"><code>&lt;textarea&gt;</code></a>, and any element with <a href="/docs/attributes/contenteditable/"><code>contenteditable</code></a></p>

<h2>Values</h2>

<table>
  <thead><tr><th>Value</th><th>Behavior</th><th>Use Case</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td><code>none</code> / <code>off</code></td><td>No automatic capitalization</td><td>Usernames, email addresses, URLs, codes</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>sentences</code></td><td>Capitalize the first letter of each sentence (the default)</td><td>General prose, comments, descriptions</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>words</code></td><td>Capitalize the first letter of each word</td><td>Name fields, titles, headings</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>characters</code></td><td>All characters uppercase</td><td>License plates, booking references, country codes</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

